<%
  bodyClass = "docs-shell";
  pageId = "docs-participant";
  pageKind = "docs";
%>

<section class="docs-container">
  <%- include('partials/brand-pill') %>

  <header class="docs-header">
    <div class="docs-badge">For participants</div>
    <h1 class="docs-title">Participant onboarding guide</h1>
    <p class="docs-lead">You received a study invite. Here’s what to expect before you share any data.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="docs-card docs-steps">
    <ol class="docs-ordered">
      <li>
        <h3>Sign in or create an account</h3>
        <p>Use your preferred email and a secure password. We only ask for extra details if the study requires them.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Join the study</h3>
        <p>Follow the invite link or paste the study code supplied by your researcher. You’ll review consent before anything else.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>Review and store consent</h3>
        <p>Download or print your consent receipt. You can revisit it, revoke it, or request deletion later.</p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-card docs-columns">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">What to look for in a consent notice</h2>
    <div class="docs-columns-grid">
      <div>
        <h4>Purpose</h4>
        <p>Why the study exists and how your contribution helps.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Data collected</h4>
        <p>The exact fields gathered, and which are optional.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Retention &amp; deletion</h4>
        <p>How long data is kept and how to request removal.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Withdrawal process</h4>
        <p>Steps to revoke consent and what happens afterwards.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <a class="docs-link" href="/signup?role=participant">Sign up as participant ↗</a>
</section>
